Error: Error: "Unable To Connect To MySQL Database Server. MySQL Said: Can'T Connect To MySQL Server On 'Localhost' (111)"

Solution: 1. Check if the MySQL service is running. Type the command `systemctl status mariadb` to check if the service is running.
2. If the service is not running, start it by typing `sudo systemctl start mariadb`.
3. Check whether the MySQL service is set to start automatically on system boot. Type `sudo systemctl enable mariadb
